WEBVTT

00:05.804 --> 00:07.471
How do you get information

00:07.506 --> 00:10.108
from someone who wants
to keep it from you?

00:10.141 --> 00:12.512
Somewhere locked
inside their brain

00:12.544 --> 00:14.413
could be the truth about a crime

00:14.446 --> 00:17.149
or the plan
for a terrorist attack

00:17.182 --> 00:18.818
or the password
to a bank account

00:18.850 --> 00:21.286
or nuclear codes.

00:21.320 --> 00:22.455
To get information,

00:22.487 --> 00:24.724
we often resort to violence,

00:26.792 --> 00:28.294
but that often doesn't work

00:28.327 --> 00:31.330
and can cause a person
to close off even more.

00:31.362 --> 00:33.365
But that's not to say
there aren't other ways

00:33.399 --> 00:34.834
of getting people to talk

00:34.866 --> 00:37.269
or even of getting their brains

00:37.302 --> 00:39.171
to talk for them.

00:39.204 --> 00:41.173
In this episode,
I'm going to be injected

00:41.207 --> 00:42.575
with a truth serum.

00:42.607 --> 00:46.244
I'm going to coerce people
into giving false confessions,

00:46.277 --> 00:48.814
and I'm going to try
to hide the truth

00:48.847 --> 00:51.183
from a mind-reading machine.

00:51.216 --> 00:52.851
What's the best way
to get the truth

00:52.884 --> 00:55.387
or detect a lie?

00:55.420 --> 00:57.522
Let's see if anybody
can dig out the secrets

00:57.555 --> 01:00.426
I've got locked up in my head.

01:26.852 --> 01:29.722
It's a classic scene
in spy movies.

01:29.755 --> 01:32.758
Someone captures someone
they want information from,

01:32.790 --> 01:34.659
they inject them
with truth serum,

01:34.692 --> 01:36.394
and the person spills

01:36.427 --> 01:37.896
all their secrets.

01:37.930 --> 01:40.565
The serum used in almost
all of these movies

01:40.599 --> 01:42.100
is Sodium Pentothal,

01:42.133 --> 01:43.501
which is an actual drug

01:43.534 --> 01:44.969
that inhibits brain activity.

01:45.002 --> 01:47.840
It was first used
as a painkiller,

01:47.873 --> 01:51.443
<i>but was found to work better
as an anti-anxiety drug.</i>

01:51.477 --> 01:53.011
<i>It dulls your thoughts,</i>

01:53.044 --> 01:55.781
<i>making it harder
to perform cognitive tasks,</i>

01:55.814 --> 01:59.552
<i>including the task
of making up a lie.</i>

01:59.585 --> 02:01.087
The use of truth serums

02:01.120 --> 02:03.588
began in 1915

02:03.621 --> 02:06.492
when Dr. Robert House,
a physician in Texas,

02:06.525 --> 02:08.560
realized that scopolamine,

02:08.594 --> 02:10.729
a drug given to women
during childbirth,

02:10.762 --> 02:13.565
<i>had the effect
of getting them to talk</i>

02:13.599 --> 02:15.133
<i>without reservation.</i>

02:15.167 --> 02:16.902
Another drug, midazolam,

02:16.935 --> 02:19.572
has been used to treat
Iraq War burn victims

02:19.605 --> 02:21.806
who suffer from PTSD.

02:21.839 --> 02:24.609
Midazolam helps reduce
their inhibitions,

02:24.643 --> 02:26.479
allowing them
to talk more freely

02:26.512 --> 02:28.581
about their experiences.

02:28.613 --> 02:31.015
Midazolam is also
one of the drugs used

02:31.048 --> 02:32.718
<i>in lethal injections,</i>

02:32.750 --> 02:35.754
<i>including several
botched executions.</i>

02:35.787 --> 02:38.757
